==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Longspur
<hw>Long"spur`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[So called from the
length of the hind claw.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any one of
several species of fringilline birds of the genus <gen>Calcarius</gen>
(or <gen>Plectrophanes</gen>), and allied genera. The Lapland longspur
(<spn>Calcarius Lapponicus</spn>), the chestnut-colored longspur
(<spn>Calcarius ornatus</spn>), and other species, inhabit the United
States.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>long-standing</ent>⟦br⟧
